data.enText: good or useful in a particular situation

data.chText: 自由贸易协定对两国都会有利。
data.enText: A free trade agreement would be advantageous to both countries.

simple_means.memory_skill: advantage 优势，有利条件 + eous 有…性质的，关于…的 → 有利的

ex.chText: 该植物在适宜的条件下会结出果子。
ex.enText: This plant will produce fruits under favourable conditions.

ex.chText: 细菌在适当的条件下繁殖很快。
ex.enText: Bacteria multiply quickly under favourable conditions.

ex.chText: 在有利于海外投资的国际环境下，这个公司获得了巨额的利润。
ex.enText: The company has made a huge profit in an international environment that is favourable to overseas investment.

synonyms.bx: 指有利于某事发生或成功的。

ex.enText: This contract is advantageous to the owners.

ex.chText: 你的对手现在处于有利地位，所以你最好更谨慎一些。
ex.enText: You'd better be more cautious, as your rival is in an advantageous position.

synonyms.bx: 指对某人、某种情况等有好处或有帮助的。

ex.chText: 这些蔬菜对人们的健康有好处。
ex.enText: These vegetables have a positive effect on people's health.

ex.chText: 海外留学对他来说是一种有益的经历。
ex.enText: Studying overseas has been a positive experience for him.

synonyms.bx: 指积极的、良好的或有所助益的。

example: a contract advantageous to our country

tr: appropriate for achieving a particular end
implies a lack of concern for fairness

value.def: If something is advantageous to you, it is likely to benefit you.

example.ex: Free exchange of goods was advantageous to all.
example.tran: 商品自由交换惠泽八方。

example.ex: ...an opportunity to purchase a set of tools at very advantageous prices.
example.tran: 以非常优惠的价格购买一套工具的机会

example.ex: They acquire the land in order to be able to sell it advantageously to the government.
example.tran: 他们购下这块土地，目的是在转手给政府时能够从中渔利。

partsOfSpeech.dec: advant 前面 + age 表名词 → 利益，好处
advantage 利益，好处 + ous 有…性质的，关于…的 → 有利的
dis 不 + advantage 利益，好处 → 缺点，不利

rootsaffixes.indicate: 表形容词，“有…性质的，关于…的”
rootsaffixes.title: -eous, -ious, -ous, -tious, -uous
